One observation from your actual Guidewire responses is particularly important. Your code expects detailed coverage information (coverage limits, deductibles, exclusions) inside the attributes.lines section of the coverage API response. In the responses you shared, that section is absent, so every financial value used for verification comes from your fallback logic (premium × 7 for coverage limit and premium × 5% for deductible). If, in the future, the Guidewire API begins returning lines with real coverage amounts and deductibles, those values will automatically override the fallback calculations, and the policy verification will use the actual policy terms instead of the proof-of-concept formulas.
